<img width="440" height="309" class="wp-image-1437817" style="width: 600px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/map-of-Kaduna-state-e1648494910291.jpg" alt="Terrorists raid 9 Kaduna villages, kill 30, abduct many, rustle 100 cows" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/map-of-Kaduna-state-e1648494910291.jpg?width=440&amp;auto_optimize=medium 440w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/map-of-Kaduna-state-e1648494910291-300x211.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w" sizes="(max-width: 440px) 100vw, 440px" /> The Giwa Local Government Council in Kaduna State has suspended the  Vice Chairman,Hon. Zubairu Alhassan for 6 months until the council investigated allegations leveled against him. Speaker of the Giwa Local Government Council’s Parliament ,Abdullahi Ismail said  at a press briefing that the Vice Chairman of the Local Government Council was suspended because of certain allegations which included alleged lack of respect to the local authority , disclosing official government secret and betrayal of trust.  However,the Vice Chairman,Hon.Zubairu Adamu denied the allegations , saying he was not even aware of being suspended.  According to the Speaker Abdullahi Ismail, 7out of 11  councillors in the Local Government Council have formed a quorum and ratified the suspension of Zubairu Alhassan as Vice Chairman of the LG Council.  Read Also: Police deploy air assets along Abuja-Kaduna Highway to fight insecurity Police deploy air assets along Abuja-Kaduna Highway to fight insecurity Declare Kaduna-Birnin-Gwari road no go area for now, Monarch advises ” We’ve unanimously agreed that he should go on suspension for a period of 6 months pending the conclusion of investigation against him,” he said. Similarly,  the Majority Leader of the LG Council and Councillor representating Kakangi Ward, Hayatu Mu’azu Dallatu, and Hon.Salisu  Junaidu  representing Panhauya ward,said the decision to suspend the Vice Chairman was taken by a majority of the councilors under the leadership of their Speaker,Hon.Abdullahi Ismail.  Also, Hon.Magaji Adamu  representing Giwa Ward, told  journalists that their resolve to suspend the Vice Chairman was backed by the Local Government reforms law, i.e Local Government Administrative Law – Kaduna State 2018, When contacted, the  Vice chairman,Hon. Zubairu Alhassan said he was not even aware of his suspension as no one has contacted him.on the matter.  According to him,people have the freedom of speech to say anything but there should be limitations because if it goes to an extent, ir could lead to litigation.  Vanguard News Nigeria